        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:01PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles southeast of Broadwater to near Gurley.
Movement was east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gurley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM MDT for
the Panhandle of Nebraska.</instruction>
